<subSubSection id="D4F9730BF48AB23C5CE23CAFB7B11C42" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="0BE949D29E52A4BDF2C7B6E698986E10" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName id="A07C0AD18CA59B99B3A1AF9D85408BC8" authorityName="Souza &amp; Funch &amp; Queiroz" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="splendida" status="comb. et stat. nov.">Hymenaea splendida</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis id="9FB6EBD0187FAC34773CE4EDAA830CF1" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">longifolia</emphasis>
Benth., Fl. Bras. (Martius) 15(2): 236. 1870. 
<taxonomicName id="8F9EF991CC1E1FFFF378FC2E57DB1BFA" authorityName="Souza &amp; Funch &amp; Queiroz" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="courbaril" status="comb. et stat. nov.">
<emphasis id="B8582FFED1AB6D48AAD79F16F076D7D4" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea courbaril</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis id="EDC2AC955A034E31F6FFBD47DC41ACE1" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">longifolia</emphasis>
(Benth.) Y.T.Lee and Andrade-Lima, J. Arnold Arbor. 55: 448. 1974. Lectotype (designated here): Brasil, Bahia, Villa de Barra, 
<emphasis id="A0576A3B48E93F219B4806E0975B99CD" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Blanchet 3135</emphasis>
(lectotype: R!, isolectotypes K!, P!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C4FE0B2746E7B557E2FF19E91482C4FC" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="112" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" type="description">
<paragraph id="4B24868E2AA261692FE8C59FFD8189AD" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DFB8E332779356D41AAC36128C0435C1" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
Medium-sized trees c. 5-12 (-18) m tall. Petiole 2.6-3 cm long; petiolule 7-8 mm long; leaflets 10.1-12.5 (-15.4) 
<normalizedToken id="965F197B99E2E2C801054E346074CAF7" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.5-6.5 (-6.9) cm, elliptic, narrow-elliptic, or oblong, not falcate, due to central vein with an angle c. 24°, apex obtuse or acute, base acute or rounded along the inner margin and rounded or slightly rounded along the outer margin, distance from the inner margin to central vein 10-11 mm in the basal region. Flower buds 2.2-3.3 cm long; flower 2.6-3.8 cm long; hypanthium 9-14 mm long; petals 1.3-2.1 cm long. Fruit oblongoid, compressed, wider at distal region, apex slightly truncate and apiculate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="220EA6779DF2993C4090CE19755C38DE" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="112" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName id="FEA8C0D91D6C94B0D9BEEB2B0FC4E49E" authorityName="I. M. Souza, Funch &amp; L. P. Queiroz" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Benth." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longifolia">
<emphasis id="F563352F241A89AB5F90EEFB58647066" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea longifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as circumscribed here, is characterized by large leaflets, both longer and wider than those of the related species 
<taxonomicName id="A455C291B7B73AF8DC40037849F40DB2" authorityName="Souza &amp; Funch &amp; Queiroz" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="courbaril">
<emphasis id="E29E2B5B10D8036C40F9E4B9ACD8A0E0" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea courbaril</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BF0EE1A16FDBC32B750C0B6E6C800682" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="altissima">
<emphasis id="989DD428CB8E06AC304841EA54D75917" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Hymenaea altissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with 
<pageBreakToken id="F592AB70A32061538A8809556FACB52F" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" start="start">longer</pageBreakToken>
petioles and petiolules (
<tableCitation id="67B4619C88AD41586ED3C7C0E3C088D3" captionStart="Table 4" captionStartId="T4" captionText="Table 4. Morphological comparison between Hymenaea courbaril, Hymenaea altissima, and Hymenaea longifolia." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/5641E2730BBF9E181E38DFF00F620044" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" tableUuid="5641E2730BBF9E181E38DFF00F620044">Table 4</tableCitation>
). The leaflets are elliptic or oblong with obtuse (rarely acute) apices and rounded bases along the outer margin (
<figureCitation id="CF1B07514AF6D7BE70434E826DE565E8" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Leaf morphology of the species recognized in the Hymenaea courbaril complex: A Hymenaea longifolia B Hymenaea courbaril C Hymenaea altissima. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10662" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Figure 3</figureCitation>
). This species occurs in Seasonally Dry Forests within the Caatinga and Cerrado phytogeographical domains in northeastern Brazil, from 
<normalizedToken id="28119D8C9095E5BD24FD20281491A4D7" originalValue="Ceará">Ceara</normalizedToken>
State to the northern portion of Bahia State.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96E17E3ECC66E6F1565C6559B28C6008" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
It was first described by 
<bibRefCitation id="B7BDBDC35B05D9B084A3FE4391AD4E0F" author="Bentham, G" journalOrPublisher="Flora Brasiliensis" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="234 - 237" refId="B4" refString="Bentham, G, 1870. Leguminosae II: Swartzieae et Caesalpinieae. In: Martius CFP (org.), Eichler AW, Urban I. Flora Brasiliensis 15 (2): 234 - 237" title="Leguminosae II: Swartzieae et Caesalpinieae. In: Martius CFP (org.), Eichler AW, Urban I." volume="15" year="1870">Bentham (1870)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="485197E21D749E1FECCD1C2F7307A002" authorityName="Souza &amp; Funch &amp; Queiroz" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="splendida">
<emphasis id="2F38713A215C738AAAA62BBD606D7504" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Hymenaea splendida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis id="8848C83DFCDA92EE91C4CEDF0422C894" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">longifolia</emphasis>
, and considered related to 
<taxonomicName id="A2E1802585242580CB8B256E4B992979" authorityName="Souza &amp; Funch &amp; Queiroz" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="courbaril">
<emphasis id="F68A67E65AF102CF288C9A1648EBA84C" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Hymenaea courbaril</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6FFA9A6A739AAFFEDAF74897A23FB2F9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stilbocarpa">
<emphasis id="C16CD6D8169CCCC29D322E63F84AB252" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Hymenaea stilbocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the glabrous leaflets, but differing from them by having larger leaflets. 
<bibRefCitation id="3CD53EF36AA2267DEBCECE7A29F8B417" author="Lee, Y-T" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Arnold Arboretum" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" refId="B22" refString="Lee, Y-T, Langenheim, JH, 1975. Systematics of the genus Hymenaea L. (Leguminosae, Caesalpinioideae, Detarieae). University of California Publications in Botany 69: 109." title="Systematics of the genus Hymenaea L. (Leguminosae, Caesalpinioideae, Detarieae). University of California Publications in Botany 69: 109." year="1975">Lee and Langenheim (1975)</bibRefCitation>
treated all these taxa under a more widely circumscribed 
<taxonomicName id="C50327BDF67379236B92B201E870AE0C" authorityName="Souza &amp; Funch &amp; Queiroz" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="courbaril">
<emphasis id="D31621BC08006F8A9F5D6233D6B96111" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Hymenaea courbaril</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a position not supported by the results presented here. Lee and Langenheim (1975: 86) misinterpreted the specimen 
<emphasis id="492AD2D79DE9CF0CD659AE71E1054731" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Blanchet 3135</emphasis>
(R) as the holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="5D13DE89B5473AEE3F8B75F2A9F63691" authorityName="Souza &amp; Funch &amp; Queiroz" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hymenaea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="splendida">
<emphasis id="E31E38D68FA5FD5E61900422868CEBFF" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Hymenaea splendida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis id="2BCBB8732672A125CEB0A7C5D011941A" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">longifolia</emphasis>
. However, when describing this variety, 
<bibRefCitation id="527E79E97F2290245B0C0556F51CE118" author="Bentham, G" journalOrPublisher="Flora Brasiliensis" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="234 - 237" refId="B4" refString="Bentham, G, 1870. Leguminosae II: Swartzieae et Caesalpinieae. In: Martius CFP (org.), Eichler AW, Urban I. Flora Brasiliensis 15 (2): 234 - 237" title="Leguminosae II: Swartzieae et Caesalpinieae. In: Martius CFP (org.), Eichler AW, Urban I." volume="15" year="1870">Bentham (1870</bibRefCitation>
: 236) cited two syntypes, 
<emphasis id="20BBEA980EE01F4CECE9B3B1C52930EE" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Blanchet 3135</emphasis>
(&quot;ad Villa da Barra prov. Bahia&quot;) and 
<emphasis id="B06331CC3F6CA388FBB2E743CE10C5DB" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Gardner 1938</emphasis>
(&quot;Serra da 
<normalizedToken id="34455DEAFC8FE879DB1A46E881F1C007" originalValue="Araripé">Araripe</normalizedToken>
, prov. Ceara&quot;). Thus, the material cited by 
<bibRefCitation id="DE47E5FC1F8A65EEB4C78BB161BE23A0" author="Lee, Y-T" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Arnold Arboretum" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" refId="B22" refString="Lee, Y-T, Langenheim, JH, 1975. Systematics of the genus Hymenaea L. (Leguminosae, Caesalpinioideae, Detarieae). University of California Publications in Botany 69: 109." title="Systematics of the genus Hymenaea L. (Leguminosae, Caesalpinioideae, Detarieae). University of California Publications in Botany 69: 109." year="1975">Lee and Langenheim (1975)</bibRefCitation>
as the holotype should be considered as a lectotype.
</paragraph>
